cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO 

This paper belongs to the intersection of computer vision and natural language processing, specifically in the area of vision-dialog navigation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, since the paper also involves language understanding and reasoning, it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, since the paper proposes a new model for learning and decision-making, it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, since the paper deals with navigation in physical environments, it could also be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics).
